  "prompt": "What can you buy with 4.95 canadian dollars on the Internet that's worth it?",
  "response": "With **4.95 Canadian dollars**, there are several worthwhile items and digital goods you can purchase online. Here are some ideas to consider:\n\n### **1. **E-Books**\n- **Platforms:** [Amazon Kindle](https://www.amazon.ca/Kindle-eBooks), [Kobo](https://www.kobo.com/)\n- **What You Get:** A wide selection of e-books across various genres. Many classics and indie titles are available for under $5.\n\n### **2. **Mobile Apps or Games**\n- **Platforms:** [Apple App Store](https://www.apple.com/app-store/), [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store)\n- **What You Get:** Premium apps, games, or in-app purchases to enhance your mobile experience.\n\n### **3. **Digital Music Tracks**\n- **Platforms:** [iTunes](https://www.apple.com/ca/itunes/), [Google Play Music](https://play.google.com/music)\n- **What You Get:** Purchase individual songs or even full albums from your favorite artists.\n\n### **4. **Streaming Service Trials or Add-Ons**\n- **Platforms:** [Spotify](https://www.spotify.com/ca-en/), [Netflix](https://www.netflix.com/ca/)\n- **What You Get:** Some platforms offer trial periods or specific add-ons that fit within your budget.\n\n### **5. **Printable Art and Templates**\n- **Platforms:** [Etsy](https://www.etsy.com/ca/), [Creative Market](https://creativemarket.com/)\n- **What You Get:** Downloadable art prints, planners, calendars, or creative templates to personalize your space or organize your life.\n\n### **6. **Digital Subscriptions or Memberships**\n- **Platforms:** [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/), niche content creators\n- **What You Get:** Access to exclusive content, newsletters, tutorials, or community forums.\n\n### **7. **Small Accessories and Gadgets**\n- **Platforms:** [AliExpress](https://www.aliexpress.com/), [eBay](https://www.ebay.ca/)\n- **What You Get:** Items like phone grips, USB gadgets, stylus pens, or other inexpensive tech accessories.\n\n### **8. **Educational Resources**\n- **Platforms:** [Udemy](https://www.udemy.com/), [Coursera](https://www.coursera.org/)\n- **What You Get:** Short courses, tutorials, or learning materials on various topics. Some courses are available at discounted rates or for free with options to pay for a certificate.\n\n### **9. **Digital Gift Cards**\n- **Platforms:** [Amazon.ca Gift Cards](https://www.amazon.ca/gift-cards), [iTunes Gift Cards](https://www.apple.com/ca/shop/gift-cards)\n- **What You Get:** Flexibility to choose what you or someone else might want to purchase later.\n\n### **10. **Craft Supplies or DIY Kits**\n- **Platforms:** [Etsy](https://www.etsy.com/ca/), [Michaels](https://www.michaels.com/)\n- **What You Get:** Small quantities of craft supplies, beads, ribbons, or DIY project kits for creative hobbies.\n\n---\n\n**Tips for Getting the Most Value:**\n\n- **Compare Prices:** Different platforms may offer the same item at varying prices. Take a moment to shop around.\n- **Look for Deals and Discounts:** Websites often have sales or discount codes that can maximize your purchasing power.\n- **Read Reviews:** Ensure the quality and value of digital products by checking user reviews and ratings.\n- **Consider Digital Over Physical:** Digital goods often provide more value at a lower cost compared to their physical counterparts.\n\nWith a budget of $4.95 CAD, focusing on digital products or small accessories typically offers the best value. Whether you're looking to indulge in some reading, enhance your device, or pick up a creative hobby, there's likely something online that fits your needs and budget.",
